      <h2>Final Verdict on PSI vs GPM</h2>
      <p>For the vast majority of commercial contracting work, GPM is the more important spec. PSI is the deciding factor only when you need to strip heavy coatings or remove bonded contaminants. For every other application — fleet washing, concrete cleaning, house washing, general cleanup — GPM determines your productivity and profitability.</p>
      <p>The ideal machine for most contractors hits both numbers: 4000+ PSI and 4.0 GPM. The <a href="https://www.amazon.com/dp/B01KZSGRTE?tag=sciencesolved-20">Simpson 4400 PSI / 4.0 GPM commercial</a> and the <a href="https://www.amazon.com/dp/B0G6SXZ7VG?tag=sciencesolved-20">Professional 4200 PSI / 4.0 GPM</a> both deliver in this class. Whichever you choose, match your nozzle, hose, and surface cleaner to the GPM spec, not the PSI spec, and you will maximize cleaning speed on every job.</p>

